==English==
===Pronunciation===
*stem, /stem/, /<tt>stem</tt>/
*:[[Rhymes:English:-ɛm|Rhymes: -ɛm]]
===Etymology===
Old English ''[[stefn]]'' (later: ''stemn'')
====Noun====
'''stem''' (pl. ''stems'')

#{{botany}} The above-ground [[stalk]] (''technically'' [[axis]]) of a vascular [[plant]], and certain anatomically similar, below-ground [[organ]]s such as [[rhizome]]s, [[bulb]]s, [[tuber]]s, and [[corm]]s.
#A narrow supporting structure on certain man-made objects, such as [[wine]] and [[champagne]] drinking [[glass]]es.
#{{linguistics}} A part of an [[uninflected]] word to which [[ending]]s may be added to form [[inflection]]s of the word.
#{{typography}} A vertical stroke of a letter.
#{{music}} A vertical stroke of a symbol representing a note in written music.
#{{nautical}} The vertical board at the bow of the boat where the planks are joined.

